observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE direct the:

1. (34) The Municipal Assessor to determine the cost of the road lot component for each road project of the LGU for recognition in the financial statements;

2. (35) The Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components of road projects;

3. (36) The Municipal Accountant to maintain the Local Road Network Ledger Cards for each component of the local road network;

4. (37) The General Services Office to complete Property Cards with the necessary data.

We recommended, and the Management agreed that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the Municipal Accountant to:
(1) Require the accountable officers, especially those with long overdue cash advances, and those outgoing officers and employees, before issuance of clearance certificate, to immediately settle or refund their unliquidated cash advance;

(2) Regularly update monitoring of all cash advances and strictly implement the non-granting of additional cash advance to officers and employees, and issue demand letters to AO with outstanding cash advance.  as of December 31, 2023; 

(3) File a request for authority to write-off dormant receivable accounts with complete necessary supporting documents, if warranted for CA involving AO  who have already died and/or absconded; 

(4)Prepare individual subsidiary ledgers for each AO with proper disclosure or classification as to whether they are still employed, have resigned or deceased, in order for the Municipality to properly plan possible course of action to undertake in the settlement of cash advances.

We recommended that the LCE, through the GAD Focal Point System of the LGU:
(28) Conduct a thorough assessment in identifying gender issues and corresponding activities that directly promote gender equality and women empowerment through the use of Harmonized Gender and Development Guidelines (HGDG) tool and to strictly adhere with the provisions of PCW-NEDA-DBM Joint Circular No. 2012-01;
(29) Submit the agency’s CY 2018 GAD Accomplishment Report to the Audit Team; (30) Plan adequately its GAD Activities to ensure that expenses adhere to the principle of prudent use of scarce financial resources of the government; and (31) Submit the lacking documentary requirements in the conduct of GAD and Women Protection Laws Training Workshop.

